===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*kʷey-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|punischen}}, from {{der|en|xno|-}}, {{der|en|fro|-}} ''puniss-'', stem of some of the conjugated forms of {{m|fro|punir}}, from {{der|en|la|puniō|t=I inflict punishment upon}}, from {{m|la|poena||punishment, penalty}}; see {{m|en|pain}}. Displaced {{ncog|ang|wītnian}} and (mostly, in this sense) {{m|ang|wrecan}}.

